---
import { Mail } from 'lucide-react'

import avatar from '@/assets/avatar.svg'
import Container from '@/components/Container.astro'
import config from '@/config.json'
import Layout from '@/layouts/Base.astro'

const { title, description } = config.pages.find((item) => item.href === '/about')!

const linkClass = 'font-medium text-foreground underline-offset-4 hover:underline'
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <Container class="mt-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tighter text-foreground sm:text-4xl">
      About
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-y-10 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_18rem] md:gap-x-16">
      <div class="order-1 overflow-hidden rounded-sm md:hidden">
        <img
          class="aspect-video w-full object-cover"
          src={avatar.src}
          alt="Wide avatar placeholder"
        />
      </div>

      <div class="order-2 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground md:order-1">
        <p>
          I'm Wren Maddox, a staff software engineer focused on distributed systems and reliability.
          I like the kind of infrastructure work that makes high-traffic systems calmer: clearer
          failure modes, less surprising latency, and fewer pages at 03:00.
        </p>

        <p>
          My path started in physics, then moved through climate-data pipelines, payments ledgers,
          observability, and real-time analytics. That arc left me with a bias for systems that can
          be explained under pressure and operated by people who are already tired.
        </p>

        <p>
          Most recently, I've been working on stream-processing and storage systems at{' '}
          <a href="https://meridian.dev" class={linkClass}>Meridian</a>, where the job is to keep a
          multi-million-events-per-second analytics platform fast, affordable, and uneventful. Before
          that, I worked on trace ingestion at{' '}
          <a href="https://lumen.io" class={linkClass}>Lumen Observability</a>, payments
          infrastructure at <a href="https://tesserapay.com" class={linkClass}>Tessera Pay</a>, and
          climate-science data systems at{' '}
          <a href="https://glacierlabs.org" class={linkClass}>Glacier Labs</a>.
        </p>

        <p>
          I mostly reach for Rust, Go, Kafka, ClickHouse, and Kubernetes these days, but I still have
          a soft spot for Python when the problem starts as a pile of data. Outside work, I build
          small projects to sharpen specific ideas, like{' '}
          <a href="https://github.com/wrenmaddox/toy-raft" class={linkClass}>toy-raft</a>{' '}
          for leader election and log replication, or{' '}
          <a href="https://github.com/wrenmaddox/plotterd" class={linkClass}>plotterd</a>{' '}
          for columnar time-series storage.
        </p>

        <p>
          I live in Lisbon and work remotely. This site is where I write through distributed-systems
          papers, production lessons, and the occasional runnable example when prose is not enough.
        </p>

        <p>
          If you want to connect, you can{' '}
          <a href={`mailto:${config.email}`} class={linkClass}>email</a>{' '}
          me or follow along on{' '}
          <a href={`https://github.com/${config.github}`} class={linkClass}>GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="order-3 md:order-2">
        <div class="w-full md:max-w-sm">
          <div class="hidden overflow-hidden rounded-sm md:block">
            <img
              class="aspect-square w-full object-cover"
              src={avatar.src}
              alt="Square avatar placeholder"
            />
          </div>
          <section class="mt-0 md:mt-8">
            <h2 class="font-medium text-muted-foreground text-xs uppercase tracking-wide">
              Experience
            </h2>
            <ol class="relative mt-4 space-y-5 border-l">
              {
                config.resume.experience.map((job) => (
                  <li class="relative pl-5">
                    <span
                      class="absolute top-1 h-3 w-3 rounded-full border-2 border-background bg-foreground"
                      style={{ left: '-6.5px' }}
                    />
                    <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-2">
                      <h3 class="font-medium text-foreground text-sm">{job.company}</h3>
                      <span class="whitespace-nowrap text-muted-foreground text-xs">
                        {job.period}
                      </span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-muted-foreground text-xs">{job.role}</p>
                  </li>
                ))
              }
            </ol>
          </section>
          <section class="mt-10 md:mt-8">
            <h2 class="font-medium text-muted-foreground text-xs uppercase tracking-wide">
              Contact
            </h2>
            <a
              href={`mailto:${config.email}`}
              class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-2 text-muted-foreground text-sm transition-colors hover:text-foreground"
            >
              <Mail width="1em" height="1em" strokeWidth={1.75} />
              {config.email}
            </a>
          </section>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>
